<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1232" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1232">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/331.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Canova</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Satillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your July 10 referred to Hanna, Villareal being in Monterey. Office here
                            assures me orders were sent to accept New York exchange at prevailing
                            gold rates and it has telegraphed Villareal substance your message.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canova</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>